@database EdgePoints.guide

@Master sD/EdgePoints.texi

@Width 72


This is the AmigaGuide® file EdgePoints.guide, produced by Makeinfo-1.55 from 
the input file sD/EdgePoints.texi.


@Node Main "EdgePoints.guide"

@{b}EdgePoints@{ub} 4.4 Contents
***********************

@Remark $VER: EdgePoints_guide 4.4 (23.2.97)

@{b}EdgePoints@{ub} is a command which can either edge detect an image and
produce a one bitplane output file or edge detect two images and
produce an ARexx script for @{b}MPMorph@{ub} to add the points.

From the GUI the @{b}O@{ub} key can be used to action the requester.  The @{b}C@{ub} or
@{b}Esc@{ub} key can be used to cancel the requester.

The shell parameters are:


 @{" FROM1/K/A            " Link "FROM1"}             First input file
 @{" FROM2/K              " Link "FROM2"}             Second input file
 @{" TO/K                 " Link "TO"}             Output file
 @{" PERCENT1=PERC1/N/K/A " Link "PERC1"}             Percentage of first file
 @{" PERCENT2=PERC2/N/K   " Link "PERC2"}             Percentage of second file
 @{" MINPOINTS=MINP/N/K   " Link "MINP"}             Number of points to add
 @{" MAXPOINTS=MAXP/N/K   " Link "MAXP"}             Number of points to test
 @{" MINDIFF/N/K          " Link "MINDIFF"}             Minimum points seperation
 @{" X/N/K/A              " Link "X"}             Width of output
 @{" Y/N/K/A              " Link "Y"}             Height of output
 @{" PUBSCREEN/K          " Link "PUBSCREEN"}             Public screen name
 @{" GRID/S               " Link "GRID"}             Random or grid

There is also a GUI with an extra gadget:


 @{" Mode gadget          " Link "Mode"}             Add Points or Edge Detect


 @{" Distribution         " Link "Distribution"}             Copyright and distribution requirements
 @{" Index                " Link "Index"}             The index for this guide


@EndNode

@Node "FROM1" "EdgePoints.guide/FROM1"
@Next "FROM2"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

FROM1/K/A - First input file
****************************

This gives the name of the first input file.

From the GUI if the @{"Mode" Link "Mode"} gadget is set to @{b}Add Points@{ub} then this defaults
to first image and can not be changed, if it is set to @{b}Edge Detect@{ub} then
it defaults to the first image but can be changed.

The @{b}I@{ub} key can be used to activate this gadget. With the @{b}right shift key@{ub}
a file requester is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "FROM2" "EdgePoints.guide/FROM2"
@Next "TO"
@Prev "FROM1"
@Toc "Main"

FROM2/K/A - Second input file
*****************************

This gives the name of the second input file.

If this is supplied then all of @{"TO" Link "TO"}, @{"PERC2" Link "PERC2"}, @{"MINP" Link "MINP"}, @{"MAXP" Link "MAXP"} and @{"MINDIFF" Link "MINDIFF"} must
be supplied

From the GUI this defaults to the second image and can not be changed.


@EndNode

@Node "TO" "EdgePoints.guide/TO"
@Next "PERC1"
@Prev "FROM2"
@Toc "Main"

TO/K - Output file
******************

If @{"FROM2" Link "FROM2"} is not supplied then this parameter is optional. If not
supplied then the edge detected image is displayed on a screen. Any key
can be pressed to stop the image being displayed. Click in the top left
corner and try again if the key is ignored.  If it is supplied then it
gives the name of the file to save the edge detected ILBM Black and
White image.

If @{"FROM2" Link "FROM2"} is supplied then this parameter must be supplied and gives the
name of the file to save the @{b}MPMorph@{ub} ARexx script.

This can not be changed from the GUI.


@EndNode

@Node "PERC1" "EdgePoints.guide/PERC1"
@Next "PERC2"
@Prev "TO"
@Toc "Main"

PERCENT1=PERC1/N/K/A - Percentage of first file
***********************************************

This gives the percentage of the first image which is considered to be
an edge.

From the GUI this defaults to 10 which is a reasonable value.

The @{b}P@{ub} key can be used to increase this value. With the @{b}shift key@{ub} the
value is decreased.


@EndNode

@Node "PERC2" "EdgePoints.guide/PERC2"
@Next "MINP"
@Prev "PERC1"
@Toc "Main"

PERCENT2=PERC2/N/K - Percentage of second file
**********************************************

When @{"FROM2" Link "FROM2"} is supplied or the @{"Mode" Link "Mode"} is set to @{b}Add Points@{ub} this gives the
percentage of the second image which is considered to be an edge.

From the GUI this defaults to 10 which is a reasonable value.

The @{b}E@{ub} key can be used to increase this value. With the @{b}shift key@{ub} the
value is decreased.


@EndNode

@Node "MINP" "EdgePoints.guide/MINP"
@Next "MAXP"
@Prev "PERC2"
@Toc "Main"

MINPOINTS=MINP/N/K - Number of points to add
********************************************

When @{"FROM2" Link "FROM2"} is supplied or the @{"Mode" Link "Mode"} is set to @{b}Add Points@{ub} this gives the
number of points which should be added to the morph. This should be
smaller than the @{"MAXP/Test Points" Link "MAXP"} value.

Depending on the @{"MINDIFF/Min Seperation" Link "MINDIFF"} value the actual number of
points may be smaller than the number requested.

From the GUI this defaults to 50 which may be a reasonable value.

The @{b}A@{ub} key can be used to increase this value. With the @{b}shift key@{ub} the
value is decreased.


@EndNode

@Node "MAXP" "EdgePoints.guide/MAXP"
@Next "MINDIFF"
@Prev "MINP"
@Toc "Main"

MAXPOINTS=MAXP/N/K - Number of points to test
*********************************************

When @{"FROM2" Link "FROM2"} is supplied or the @{"Mode" Link "Mode"} is set to @{b}Add Points@{ub} this gives the
number of points which are tested. This should be larger than the
@{"MINP/Add Points" Link "MINP"} value.

If the @{"GRID/Grid" Link "GRID"} parameter is provided/gadget is selected then this
number of points is initially added in a square grid, otherwise they
are added randomly.

From the GUI this defaults to 150 which may be a reasonable value.

The @{b}T@{ub} key can be used to increase this value. With the @{b}shift key@{ub} the
value is decreased.


@EndNode

@Node "MINDIFF" "EdgePoints.guide/MINDIFF"
@Next "X"
@Prev "MAXP"
@Toc "Main"

MINDIFF/N/K - Minimum points seperation
***************************************

When @{"FROM2" Link "FROM2"} is supplied or the @{"Mode" Link "Mode"} is set to @{b}Add Points@{ub} this gives the
minimum seperation of points to add to the morph.

From the GUI this defaults to 5 which may be a reasonable value.

The @{b}S@{ub} key can be used to increase this value. With the @{b}shift key@{ub} the
value is decreased.


@EndNode

@Node "X" "EdgePoints.guide/X"
@Next "Y"
@Prev "MINDIFF"
@Toc "Main"

X/N/K/A - Width of output
*************************

This gives the width of the output. The input images are scaled to this
size.

From the GUI this defaults to the width of the morph and can not be
changed.


@EndNode

@Node "Y" "EdgePoints.guide/Y"
@Next "PUBSCREEN"
@Prev "X"
@Toc "Main"

Y/N/K/A - Height of output
**************************

This gives the height of the output. The input images are scaled to
this size.

From the GUI this defaults to the height of the morph and can not be
changed.


@EndNode

@Node "GRID" "EdgePoints.guide/GRID"
@Next "Mode"
@Prev "PUBSCREEN"
@Toc "Main"

GRID/S - Random or grid
***********************

If this parameter is supplied/gadget selected then points are initially
added in a grid. Otherwise they are added at random.

From the GUI this defaults to selected. The @{b}G@{ub} key toggles the selection.


@EndNode

@Node "PUBSCREEN" "EdgePoints.guide/PUBSCREEN"
@Next "GRID"
@Prev "Y"
@Toc "Main"

PUBSCREEN/K - Public screen name
********************************

This parameter can be used to select a screen on which to display
progress requesters.

From the GUI this defaults to the screen that @{b}MPMorph@{ub} is running on and
can not be changed.


@EndNode

@Node "Mode" "EdgePoints.guide/Mode"
@Next "Distribution"
@Prev "GRID"
@Toc "Main"

Add Points or Edge Detect
*************************

This gadget defaults to @{b}Add Points@{ub} which add points to the morph. It
can also be set to @{b}Edge Detect@{ub} which displays the result of edge
detecting an image.

The @{b}M@{ub} key can be used to cycle this gadget.


@EndNode

